.SH NAME
evolve-view - Browse the stored results in a web browser (filter, sort, snapshot)


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBevolve view [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Serve the committed results as an interactive web report: filter by provider, model, plugin, skill, type, and pass/fail; sort and toggle between per-case and rollup views; and save a self-contained HTML snapshot of the current view.

.PP
The server is read-only and binds to localhost. While it runs it watches the results files, so a concurrent \fBevolve run\fR (or any process that rewrites them) refreshes an open browser. With --out it writes a snapshot file and exits without serving.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for view

.PP
\fB--no-open\fP[=false]
	do not open the report in a browser

.PP
\fB--out\fP=""
	write a self-contained HTML snapshot to this path and exit (no server)

.PP
\fB--port\fP=0
	localhost port to serve on (default: pick a free port)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--json\fP[=false]
	emit machine-readable JSONL progress on stdout

.PP
\fB--layout\fP="auto"
	repository layout: auto, marketplace, multi, or single

.PP
\fB--results-format\fP=""
	format for results files and the EVALUATION rollup: json, jsonc, or yaml (default: config results_format or json)

.PP
\fB--root\fP=""
	repository root to operate on (default: walk up from the current directory)

.PP
\fB--telemetry-dir\fP=""
	write OpenTelemetry traces/metrics/logs as JSON to this directory (default: off; overrides OTEL_* env vars)

.PP
\fB-v\fP, \fB--verbose\fP[=false]
	enable debug logging


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBevolve(1)\fP
